1 - Summary

In the following sections, you will find the KEGG Pathway enrichment. The input data for those analyis is the output of the RNADiff analysis where adjusted p-values above 0.05 are excluded. Moreover, we removed candidates with log2 fold change below 1. Using these filters, the list of differentially expressed genes is made of 15 up and 38 down genes (total 53)

In the following plots you can find the first KEGG Pathways that are enriched, keeping a maximum of 15 pathways.

The KEGG name used is ebe.

This table gives you (column N) the number of genes used when performing the enrichment on up-regulated genes (up), down-regulated genes, and when we take all up and down regulated genes (all). We also provide the total number of genes that were analysed in the differential analysis (all genes). This number may be lower that the number of genes found in the annotation if a filter was applied. Finally, using those genes, we provide the percentage of those genes that were found in the KEGG database. the Enrichment analysis relies on a background. This background was defined as 4600 

category,mapped_percentage,N
down,9.736842E+01,38
up,6.666667E+01,15
all,8.867925E+01,53
